1
00:00:01,380 --> 00:00:04,960
[Episode 1: A Wish Born of Despair]

2
00:00:13,740 --> 00:00:14,940
I did my best.

3
00:00:14,940 --> 00:00:16,079
You did your best?

4
00:00:16,079 --> 00:00:16,950
I did my best, too.

5
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:19,210
It was already too late when I took over.

6
00:00:19,210 --> 00:00:21,250
It was already too late when you took over？

7
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:22,710
Can you just give me one more chance?

8
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:24,020
Then who's gonna give me a chance?

9
00:00:24,020 --> 00:00:25,250
You are not suited for this industry.

10
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:26,650
He's so bad I don't even know what to say.

11
00:00:26,650 --> 00:00:28,120
Why don't you consider a career change?

12
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:30,720
Haven't you considered
going to a cram school?

13
00:00:32,729 --> 00:00:33,960
He is absent from every sketching class.

14
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:35,430
Honestly, it's better if he's not there.

15
00:00:35,430 --> 00:00:37,070
I've cleaned up enough
of your mess already.

16
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:38,100
What are you trying to say?

17
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,330
Why can't we just work hard

18
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:40,400
and get better together?

19
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:42,060
I honestly think he's just...

20
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:48,310
1, 4 ,2, 8, 5, 7.

21
00:01:37,090 --> 00:01:40,289
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

22
00:01:57,690 --> 00:02:00,160
Come on, we have arrived at Xingpu Island.

23
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:01,910
Let's get our luggage up ahead.

24
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:03,180
What do we have

25
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:04,440
the most of here?

26
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:06,370
The sea turtles.

27
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:09,400
The ice shop on the hill is also delicious.

28
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:10,729
Besides

29
00:02:10,729 --> 00:02:12,690
snorkeling and the ice shop,

30
00:02:12,690 --> 00:02:14,420
what else do you want to do here?

31
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,329
Listen—

32
00:02:19,829 --> 00:02:20,840
Besides the ocean,

33
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,400
there is very little light pollution
on the mountain at night.

34
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,970
You can ride a bike up the mountain.

35
00:02:24,970 --> 00:02:27,900
Maybe you will see a shooting star
and can make a wish.

36
00:02:29,770 --> 00:02:30,640
Hong.

37
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:31,370
Hong.

38
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:32,579
I am telling you,

39
00:02:32,579 --> 00:02:33,850
I'm really damn good at playing guitar—

40
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:36,140
[Stairway Corner Ice]

41
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,290
Today's fruit is really sweet.

42
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:38,990
-The seasons are important.
-You're all here.

43
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:39,920
Village Chief.

44
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,120
-Village Chief, you're here.
-The Village Chief is here.

45
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:41,690
Just in time, just in time.

46
00:02:41,690 --> 00:02:42,560
Come.

47
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:50,829
Village Chief, have some fruit.

48
00:02:50,829 --> 00:02:51,770
Okay, thank you.

49
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:52,730
I will get you a fork.

50
00:02:52,730 --> 00:02:53,800
Don't be so polite.

51
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:55,470
I will get a fork for you.

52
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:56,100
Thank you.

53
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,040
It is super sweet.

54
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:57,740
Wanzhe.

55
00:02:58,050 --> 00:02:59,180
You're up.

56
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,170
Li Wanzhe.

57
00:03:00,210 --> 00:03:01,940
You're only coming down now?

58
00:03:01,940 --> 00:03:03,040
You're hitting me first thing
in the morning?

59
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,640
What about your reputation?

60
00:03:06,650 --> 00:03:07,280
Hama-chan.

61
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:07,810
Morning.

62
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,470
Won't your stomach hurt
eating shaved ice this early?

63
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,500
I like it.

64
00:03:13,430 --> 00:03:14,430
Suit yourself.

65
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,990
Deliver 5 bowls of shaved ice later

66
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:20,140
to the pier.

67
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,000
Okay.

68
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,500
Then, when you go to the main island today,

69
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,630
help me stop by the fishing harbor

70
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:25,490
to buy some turtle-shaped cakes.

71
00:03:31,770 --> 00:03:33,410
1, 2, 3, 4.

72
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:39,240
Alright, back to work!

73
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:48,820
Xiangyong!

74
00:03:48,820 --> 00:03:50,230
Xiangyong, why are you back?

75
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:51,530
I missed you so much.

76
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,060
Dad.

77
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:54,130
Old man.

78
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,780
My idol is back.

79
00:03:58,570 --> 00:03:59,340
Xiangyong.

80
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:00,960
Watermelon candy.

81
00:04:01,170 --> 00:04:02,340
Your favorite.

82
00:04:06,610 --> 00:04:07,710
Thank you, Hong.

83
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:10,250
I'm not into watermelon candy anymore.

84
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,150
Then...

85
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:13,780
what about sea turtles and drawing?

86
00:04:13,850 --> 00:04:14,820
Do you still like them?

87
00:04:14,820 --> 00:04:15,550
Xiangyong.

88
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:16,420
Oh, Xiangyong.

89
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:17,850
Mr. De.

90
00:04:17,850 --> 00:04:19,250
It has been a long time.

91
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:21,589
Weren't you going abroad
for some exhibition?

92
00:04:21,589 --> 00:04:22,590
-No.
-Xiangyong.

93
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:25,230
Come in and chat with me more.

94
00:04:25,230 --> 00:04:26,160
Okay, I will talk to you next time.

95
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,400
Xiangyong is busy.

96
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,800
-Don't keep dragging him.
-I'm leaving. Thank you.

97
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,670
-Hey, this is my chance to pursue my dream.
-Are you really not eating?

98
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:31,730
Why did you interrupt me?

99
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:32,830
Hey, chase my ass.

100
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,440
-Xiangyong is Xiangyong. And you?
-You'll pay for my trip to the main island, right?

101
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,340
No way. Pay for what?

102
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:37,040
Get back to work.

103
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,700
The money for the boat ticket.

104
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:43,080
Village Chief, you are really great.

105
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,950
All 5 of us in our family
will vote for you.

106
00:04:44,950 --> 00:04:45,750
You have to keep your word.

107
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:46,950
When I am Village Chief,

108
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:48,150
the streets are clean,

109
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:49,220
and the gutters are cleared.

110
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:50,450
-I will vote for you.
-Is that Xiangyong?

111
00:04:50,450 --> 00:04:51,490
Xiangyong.

112
00:04:51,490 --> 00:04:52,320
Xiangyong is back.

113
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,420
It is Xiangyong.

114
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:54,560
Xiangyong.

115
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,620
It was hard for him to make it back.

116
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:56,659
You are back!

117
00:04:56,659 --> 00:04:58,190
Xiangyong, how do you have time to come back?
Come here, come here.

118
00:04:58,190 --> 00:04:58,830
Xiangyong.

119
00:04:58,830 --> 00:05:00,130
Have you published a book yet?

120
00:05:00,130 --> 00:05:01,700
He was the one
who held an art exhibition last time.

121
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:02,530
Right, we even went there.

122
00:05:02,530 --> 00:05:03,300
I didn't hold an art exhibition.

123
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:03,830
Yes, you did.

124
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:05,900
I always tell my younger brother
to be like you.

125
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:07,600
You are really amazing.

126
00:05:09,570 --> 00:05:10,670
Let me take some photos.

127
00:05:10,670 --> 00:05:13,000
He is the best at drawing
on Xingpu Island.

128
00:05:13,010 --> 00:05:14,910
I've watched him grow up
since he was little.

129
00:05:14,910 --> 00:05:16,080
-He Xiangyong.
-Be careful.

130
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,150
-Come here!
-Watch the car!

131
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:34,659
Thanks.

132
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:37,000
Come on.

133
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,800
We've known each other for so long—

134
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,230
We're totally in sync.

135
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:43,200
You know, those residents on our island

136
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,670
have nothing better to do

137
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:46,270
than gossip.

138
00:05:46,770 --> 00:05:48,170
But there is no other way.

139
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:50,680
You are the pride of Xingpu Island.

140
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,340
I originally wanted to go find you
for a bowl of jelly ice.

141
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:58,200
It is fine.

142
00:05:58,350 --> 00:06:00,080
I will pack a bowl for you later.

143
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,890
You came back so suddenly this time.

144
00:06:03,890 --> 00:06:05,750
Why didn't you tell me in advance?

145
00:06:08,330 --> 00:06:09,460
You said it was sudden.

146
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:11,600
How was I supposed to tell you in advance?

147
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,900
That is true.

148
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:17,140
I bet you missed me.

149
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:18,710
Listen,

150
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:20,350
while you were away,

151
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,140
my mom was so annoying.

152
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:24,310
She kept saying He Xiangyong is great,

153
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:26,180
going to the main island
to fulfill his dreams.

154
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:26,950
And then she said

155
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:29,220
I only stay in that tiny room
playing video games

156
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:30,750
and told me to look up to you.

157
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:32,950
I am almost sick of hearing it.

158
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,820
Village Chief Wang

159
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:35,990
is planning to build a resort

160
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:37,290
and set up solar power projects.

161
00:06:37,290 --> 00:06:38,659
I strongly suspect

162
00:06:38,659 --> 00:06:40,590
he wants to run for Township Mayor.

163
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:50,230
We're here.

164
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,600
Mr. He.

165
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,370
Mr. He.

166
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,090
Dudu, have you seen Mr. He?

167
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,290
Where are the others?

168
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:20,070
Mr. He.

169
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:23,300
Your He Xiangyong is back.

170
00:07:24,770 --> 00:07:26,410
I know. I know.

171
00:07:26,930 --> 00:07:29,590
Your mom broadcast it
in the group chat long ago.

172
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,390
Mom.

173
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,610
I am back.

174
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,220
Are you hungry?

175
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:04,280
How about I make you some noodles?

176
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,010
Okay.

177
00:08:09,350 --> 00:08:10,490
I'm not hungry.

178
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:16,010
This scrap wood wasn't here last time.

179
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:18,460
If you aren't going to use it,
why pick it up?

180
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:20,190
You don't even put away
the storage baskets and brooms.

181
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:21,990
What kind of guesthouse is this?

182
00:08:23,380 --> 00:08:25,840
And you're drinking
so early in the morning.

183
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:30,000
Come on.

184
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,010
How many times do you even
come back in a year?

185
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:34,210
And you come back with that face?

186
00:08:35,230 --> 00:08:36,780
If you don't want to come back,

187
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:38,039
don't force yourself.

188
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,080
No, Mr. He.

189
00:08:40,650 --> 00:08:42,780
He is just too busy and tired from work.

190
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,950
The waves were big this morning,
and he got seasick.

191
00:08:44,950 --> 00:08:45,920
He didn't mean it.

192
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,760
Poor thing, tired.

193
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,020
Aren't you tired from work?

194
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:49,820
Yes.

195
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:50,630
I am also very tired.

196
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:51,830
Dudu is also very tired.

197
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:52,690
Who isn't, huh?

198
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,910
Everyone is tired from work.

199
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,460
Today isn't even a day off.

200
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:58,070
He came back on a workday,

201
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:59,270
and you told me he's tired?

202
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,500
I'm telling you,

203
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,670
I am also a boss.

204
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:04,110
If I found an employee

205
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:05,670
as lazy and messy as him,

206
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,810
do you know how unlucky I would be?

207
00:09:06,810 --> 00:09:08,540
-You have to...
-Yeah.

208
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,850
I am just lazy and messy.

209
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:13,280
If you don't want to look at me,

210
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:14,260
then don't look.

211
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,520
You can just pretend I didn't come back.

212
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,650
I didn't ask you to come back.

213
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:19,150
You're the one
who skipped work to come back

214
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:20,450
and then showed me a grumpy face.

215
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:21,520
If I don't come back, you'll scold me.

216
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:22,560
If I do come back, you will still scold me.

217
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,290
Didn't I get this face from you?

218
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:25,030
Look—

219
00:09:25,030 --> 00:09:25,990
Every time I come back,
it's the same with you.

220
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:26,630
Okay.

221
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:27,700
Stop.

222
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:30,130
1m 10.09s.

223
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:32,590
Congrats, you just broke
your record again.

224
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:33,700
Congratulations.

225
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:34,760
Congratulations.

226
00:09:36,570 --> 00:09:38,040
Alright, don't be angry.

227
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,280
Hey.

228
00:09:44,010 --> 00:09:45,150
Don't be angry.

229
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:46,680
Come on, cheers, Mr. He.

230
00:09:46,930 --> 00:09:47,470
Cheers.

231
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:50,140
Drink my ass.

232
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:06,630
Got nothing better to do?

233
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,850
Shouldn't you be at the shop?

234
00:10:11,970 --> 00:10:12,810
No.

235
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:14,540
My mom told me to tell you

236
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:16,610
that our Village Chief
is hosting a banquet today.

237
00:10:16,610 --> 00:10:17,810
Xiangyong just happened to come back,

238
00:10:17,810 --> 00:10:19,210
so she said you must come.

239
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:22,320
Mr. He.

240
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,140
I'll go back to work first.

241
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:30,690
Sorry.

242
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:34,460
The chair.

243
00:10:38,850 --> 00:10:39,790
Thank you.

244
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:41,640
He Xiangyong.

245
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,900
You must come tonight.

246
00:10:52,850 --> 00:10:53,880
Come on.

247
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,120
Drink, drink.

248
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,450
Thank you.

249
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:57,950
I have served you for all this time,

250
00:10:57,950 --> 00:10:58,650
right?

251
00:10:58,650 --> 00:10:59,650
You all know it,

252
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:00,420
right?

253
00:11:00,420 --> 00:11:01,390
You must vote for me.

254
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:02,220
Okay?

255
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:03,900
Is that a deal?

256
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,760
Vote for me, okay?

257
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:06,660
Please.

258
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:08,200
Enjoy your meal.

259
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,070
Take your time.

260
00:11:09,730 --> 00:11:11,270
It is so delicious.

261
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,530
Eat well.

262
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:14,600
Eat well.

263
00:11:15,210 --> 00:11:16,280
Enjoy it.

264
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:17,570
Let me see.

265
00:11:17,570 --> 00:11:19,040
No, not this song.

266
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:21,140
I want...

267
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:23,210
24206.

268
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:25,280
-78257.
-Okay, I'll select them for you.

269
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:26,350
I'm not done yet.

270
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:27,420
27394.

271
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:28,280
Thank you!

272
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,250
Remember to vote for me.

273
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:30,120
Thank you.

274
00:11:32,690 --> 00:11:33,490
Mr. He.

275
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:37,430
When is your son going to America

276
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:40,130
or Europe to hold an art exhibition?

277
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:41,730
Yeah right, try making it to Luzhou first.

278
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:42,300
Don't say that.

279
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:43,260
Come, drink, drink.

280
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:45,570
What kind of paintings does he even paint?

281
00:11:45,570 --> 00:11:46,830
I am not too sure, either.

282
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:47,400
Eat more.

283
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,570
Come, Xiangyong.

284
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:49,570
Eat more.

285
00:11:49,570 --> 00:11:50,820
You haven't eaten anything.

286
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:51,710
He.

287
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:54,110
The helper at your place didn't come today?

288
00:11:54,210 --> 00:11:55,310
It's his day off.

289
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:57,940
He went off somewhere early this morning.

290
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:01,010
Since when did we have a helper?

291
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:02,520
Well,

292
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,090
he has been here for a while.

293
00:12:04,090 --> 00:12:06,720
And he is really handsome.

294
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:08,820
He's a "young hunk,"

295
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:09,860
right?

296
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:10,560
He's not bad.

297
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,360
But,

298
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:14,260
he managed to last more
than 3 days at my house?

299
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,430
Watch your words.

300
00:12:16,630 --> 00:12:17,500
He has a good personality

301
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:19,030
and is easy to get along with—

302
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,070
unlike you.

303
00:12:20,070 --> 00:12:20,700
You're so hard to get along with.

304
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,300
What's with that face all day?

305
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,200
I'm not making a face.

306
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,240
You're literally doing it right now.

307
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,570
You are the easiest to get along with.

308
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:26,840
Come on, let's not argue while eating.

309
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,440
OK.

310
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,210
Right.

311
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:28,740
Come.

312
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:29,340
Come, come, come.

313
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:30,480
Listen to the doctor.

314
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,080
Those who don't know
how to talk shouldn't talk.

315
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:32,950
Let's drink.

316
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:33,980
Let's drink.

317
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,820
Come, drink.

318
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:37,020
Let's drink.

319
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:41,150
Village Chief Wang.

320
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,760
Let's sing together.

321
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,560
You sing.

322
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:46,130
Let's sing together.

323
00:12:46,130 --> 00:12:47,390
This is a good song.

324
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,420
This is my signature song.

325
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,700
What's wrong? You're not eating?

326
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:00,850
It's too hot.

327
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:02,210
I don't have much of an appetite.

328
00:13:02,210 --> 00:13:03,610
No appetite?

329
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:04,910
Don't think I can't tell.

330
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:06,910
It's obviously because of your dad.

331
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:10,020
If your mom spoke to you like that,

332
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:11,480
would you be able to smile?

333
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:12,620
I could.

334
00:13:12,620 --> 00:13:13,690
I wouldn't care.

335
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:17,660
Wanzhe.

336
00:13:19,860 --> 00:13:21,030
Long time no see.

337
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,220
Do you want to eat something here?

338
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:29,940
OK.

339
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:32,910
Help me clear the level when you get back.

340
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:34,570
Don't eat the stuff in my room.

341
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,370
I'll think about it.

342
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:37,610
Think about it?

343
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:39,860
Don't eat it!

344
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,810
Are you going to study in Japan?

345
00:13:44,820 --> 00:13:45,650
No.

346
00:13:45,650 --> 00:13:46,990
You're planning a trip to Japan?

347
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:47,990
I have no money.

348
00:13:47,990 --> 00:13:49,990
Then why are you so close to Xiaohai?

349
00:13:49,990 --> 00:13:51,160
He is so cold

350
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,290
and talks so little.

351
00:13:52,690 --> 00:13:54,200
It is good that he talks little.

352
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,760
How peaceful it is for my ears.

353
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:56,660
Look, my mom—

354
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:58,120
One of her is enough for me.

355
00:13:59,170 --> 00:13:59,900
I want to sing.

356
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:00,530
Sing!

357
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:02,440
What are you singing?

358
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,160
What are you singing? Come on.

359
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:05,740
An English song.

360
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,560
Tell me,

361
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,570
how long are you staying this time?

362
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,280
Probably

363
00:14:12,850 --> 00:14:14,080
for quite a while.

364
00:14:14,550 --> 00:14:15,680
What does that mean?

365
00:14:15,850 --> 00:14:17,850
Did you use up all your annual leave?

366
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:20,350
I don't have annual leave anymore.

367
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:21,950
You don't have annual leave?

368
00:14:22,410 --> 00:14:23,500
Are you using special leave?

369
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,800
No.

370
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:25,460
Then what?

371
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,060
I don't have a job anymore.

372
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,160
I can't hear you.

373
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,740
I was fired!

374
00:14:34,740 --> 00:14:35,500
A song—

375
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:46,130
I think I'll sing a Taiwanese song instead.

376
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:47,180
A Taiwanese one is good.

377
00:14:47,180 --> 00:14:48,880
I also think I should sing
a Taiwanese song.

378
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:49,720
Chen Lei's.

379
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:50,420
Sing Chen Lei's.

380
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:51,250
I'll select it.

381
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,320
Okay?

382
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:52,720
Everyone sing together.

383
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:53,420
Eat up.

384
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:54,660
-Hurry up and sing.
-Drink.

385
00:14:54,660 --> 00:14:55,660
Hurry up and sing.

386
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:57,630
I'll sing Chen Lei's

387
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,490
"Happiness Is All That Matters."

388
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:01,720
He Xiangyong.

389
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,360
Drink.

390
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:06,550
Come on.

391
00:15:06,860 --> 00:15:07,690
Come.

392
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,800
It's okay.

393
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,990
Where is the instructor?

394
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:07,590
Happy birthday to you.

395
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,840
Good thing I am smart enough

396
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:18,040
to know you were here.

397
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,440
Look.

398
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,640
There are so many shooting stars today.

399
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:33,850
I really miss this.

400
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,190
Do you remember?

401
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,290
We used to come here often
to make wishes when we were little.

402
00:16:37,290 --> 00:16:39,590
Every time you said
you wanted to be a great painter.

403
00:16:39,590 --> 00:16:41,320
Actually, I really admire you.

404
00:16:43,830 --> 00:16:45,360
What do you admire about me?

405
00:16:47,330 --> 00:16:49,070
I am not a painter now.

406
00:16:50,650 --> 00:16:52,850
I don't even have the right to hold a pen.

407
00:16:54,070 --> 00:16:55,510
Everyone kept talking about

408
00:16:55,510 --> 00:16:57,240
Europe and France.

409
00:16:58,610 --> 00:16:59,950
It's hilarious.

410
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:03,080
I even got fired
from being a simple editor.

411
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:04,780
And I still owe...

412
00:17:11,290 --> 00:17:14,089
Anyway, you don't need to envy
this kind of pathetic life.

413
00:17:14,089 --> 00:17:15,500
I'm so done with this.

414
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:19,300
I wish I didn't have to be
He Xiangyong anymore.

415
00:17:20,099 --> 00:17:21,500
Hey, you've been speaking very quietly.

416
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,800
Can you speak louder?

417
00:17:24,099 --> 00:17:25,210
I said,

418
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:28,010
I wish I didn't have
to be He Xiangyong anymore!

419
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:28,980
That's easy.

420
00:17:28,980 --> 00:17:30,240
Just jump into the sea.

421
00:17:33,130 --> 00:17:34,000
Good idea.

422
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:34,720
It is.

423
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:35,280
Let's go.

424
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:35,980
Together.

425
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:38,350
Right here.

426
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:40,650
No, no, no, I'm kidding.

427
00:17:41,190 --> 00:17:42,090
I'm not kidding.

428
00:17:42,090 --> 00:17:42,860
Let's go. We'll jump together.

429
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:43,820
No, I'm really kidding.

430
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:44,320
I'm sorry. I didn't...

431
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:45,150
I'll just jump.

432
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:47,010
Then He Xiangyong can start over!

433
00:17:55,470 --> 00:17:56,970
Really...

434
00:17:56,970 --> 00:17:59,110
If I hadn't known you
for over 20 years,

435
00:17:59,410 --> 00:18:01,180
I would push you down right now.

436
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:03,900
Let me help you.

437
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:28,740
Uncle Hua?

438
00:18:28,970 --> 00:18:29,800
You're back.

439
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,660
You haven't gone back yet?

440
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:34,440
Goodnight.

441
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,580
Xiangyong.

442
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:39,780
I cooked this for you.

443
00:18:40,660 --> 00:18:43,520
Your dad was worried
you didn't eat enough tonight.

444
00:18:44,220 --> 00:18:45,250
He was drunk

445
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,720
but insisted on cooking
garlic shrimp vermicelli for you.

446
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,460
I was worried he would blow up
the whole kitchen.

447
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:50,870
I told him to go to sleep

448
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:52,030
and that I would handle it.

449
00:18:52,030 --> 00:18:53,490
So eat some in a bit.

450
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:56,900
Thank you, Uncle Hua.

451
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:57,760
Wait a second.

452
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:00,770
Vermicelli.

453
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:06,570
This brat.

454
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:08,930
Don't come back.

455
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:18,380
I can't guarantee the taste.

456
00:19:34,470 --> 00:19:35,500
What's wrong?

457
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:38,670
Is there not enough garlic?

458
00:19:38,670 --> 00:19:39,570
I'll go get more...

459
00:19:39,570 --> 00:19:40,810
No, Uncle Hua.

460
00:19:41,610 --> 00:19:42,640
It's delicious.

461
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,880
I thought you were eating so gloomily.

462
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:47,650
What is it?

463
00:19:47,650 --> 00:19:48,850
Are you in a bad mood?

464
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,050
I just remembered

465
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:54,960
when I was little,

466
00:19:55,690 --> 00:19:58,430
it was only when there was
something worth celebrating at home

467
00:19:58,430 --> 00:20:01,200
that my dad would cook
garlic shrimp vermicelli for me.

468
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,500
But today...

469
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:05,450
Uncle Hua,

470
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,840
did I disappoint my dad?

471
00:20:11,470 --> 00:20:12,570
Xiangyong.

472
00:20:13,470 --> 00:20:14,910
When young people enter society,

473
00:20:14,910 --> 00:20:16,840
it's natural to have ups and downs.

474
00:20:17,510 --> 00:20:20,410
It's impossible for everything
to go smoothly forever.

475
00:20:20,410 --> 00:20:21,920
Back when I was in the big hospital,

476
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,050
it was the same.

477
00:20:24,150 --> 00:20:25,410
Only through setbacks

478
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:27,420
can one grow in life.

479
00:20:30,090 --> 00:20:31,050
I just...

480
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:35,800
Anyway, I feel like

481
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:37,970
my current self

482
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,930
is useless.

483
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:44,540
You have to see
what it is you are pursuing.

484
00:20:44,540 --> 00:20:45,840
Is it being useful?

485
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:47,710
Or being liked?

486
00:20:48,910 --> 00:20:49,810
Or perhaps,

487
00:20:50,210 --> 00:20:52,310
it's enough that you like yourself?

488
00:20:53,510 --> 00:20:55,080
You should know that parents

489
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,520
are easily satisfied.

490
00:20:57,150 --> 00:20:58,590
As long as their child is doing well,

491
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:00,050
they ask for nothing else.

492
00:21:00,990 --> 00:21:01,780
So,

493
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:06,060
don't take your father's harsh words
to heart.

494
00:21:08,490 --> 00:21:10,850
He is actually very happy you are back.

495
00:21:13,070 --> 00:21:14,330
Is he?

496
00:21:14,970 --> 00:21:16,340
Is he happy?

497
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,740
Don't just look with your eyes,

498
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:20,400
feel with your heart instead.

499
00:21:22,580 --> 00:21:23,880
Listen.

500
00:21:25,010 --> 00:21:26,680
Find some time

501
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,210
to have a good talk with him.

502
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,050
Sometimes,

503
00:21:30,050 --> 00:21:31,520
the one who gives in

504
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,320
isn't the one who loses.

505
00:21:35,590 --> 00:21:37,260
But you know,

506
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:39,430
when the two of us talk,

507
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:41,460
it's hard to last more than 3 sentences.

508
00:21:41,460 --> 00:21:42,400
Then don't rush.

509
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,260
Take your time.

510
00:21:44,770 --> 00:21:46,430
Sometimes when things happen,

511
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,440
they aren't necessarily bad things.

512
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,500
Let's look at it from another angle.

513
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,090
Maybe,

514
00:21:51,070 --> 00:21:52,810
maybe it's a chance from God

515
00:21:52,810 --> 00:21:54,310
to make some changes.

516
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:57,170
It just depends on
whether you seize it or not.

517
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,380
Alright, eat up,

518
00:21:59,710 --> 00:22:01,510
or the vermicelli will get cold.

519
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:02,850
No matter what,

520
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:04,120
I will support you.

521
00:22:05,890 --> 00:22:07,090
Thank you, Uncle Hua.

522
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:09,120
Well...

523
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:10,620
Do you want more garlic?

524
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:11,830
No, thanks.

525
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:12,790
Are you sure?

526
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,540
How about

527
00:22:13,740 --> 00:22:15,070
I add some chili?

528
00:22:15,160 --> 00:22:15,960
Okay.

529
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,280
Why isn't he back yet?

530
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:36,810
It's already late at night.

531
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:51,950
[Beautify the Home Painting Competition]

532
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:54,330
[Xingpu Island Junior Ironman Competition]

533
00:23:25,130 --> 00:23:27,110
Who said growing up is great?

534
00:23:31,270 --> 00:23:32,910
That's bullshit.

535
00:23:34,470 --> 00:23:36,540
Growing up isn't good at all.

536
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,080
It sucks so bad.

537
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,020
Who is it?

538
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:27,350
You should know that parents

539
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:28,610
are easily satisfied.

540
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:30,360
As long as their child is doing well,

541
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:31,820
they ask for nothing else.

542
00:25:38,930 --> 00:25:39,700
Good heavens.

543
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:40,960
How did it get so heavy?

544
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:42,680
It's too heavy.

545
00:25:42,740 --> 00:25:44,200
Hurry and help me.

546
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,170
Chen Haowei!

547
00:25:46,740 --> 00:25:47,500
Coming.

548
00:26:11,350 --> 00:26:13,410
Hello, I am Chen Haowei, from Class 2.

549
00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:16,440
From that day on,

550
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:17,500
He Xiangyong!

551
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:19,140
I decided

552
00:26:19,470 --> 00:26:20,240
He Xiangyong!

553
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:21,110
that this name

554
00:26:21,110 --> 00:26:23,680
-has nothing to do with me anymore.
-Chen Haowei.

555
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:24,780
Don't come looking for me ever again.

556
00:26:24,780 --> 00:26:26,510
I never thought I'd bring it up…

557
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:30,210
until...

558
00:26:31,350 --> 00:26:32,860
we met again.

559
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:46,270
[Epilogue]

560
00:27:00,550 --> 00:27:01,050
Hey.

561
00:27:01,050 --> 00:27:02,280
The instructor is here.
You're not leaving?

562
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:03,120
The instructor is here.

563
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:04,180
The instructor is here, up there.

564
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:04,880
Let's go.

565
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:05,890
What are you doing?

566
00:27:05,890 --> 00:27:07,390
What on earth are you doing?

567
00:27:07,390 --> 00:27:08,890
Where is the instructor?

568
00:27:08,990 --> 00:27:09,870
Still running?

569
00:27:11,190 --> 00:27:12,390
Let's go. He's right behind us.

570
00:27:12,390 --> 00:27:13,460
Where is the instructor?

571
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:14,260
Behind us.

572
00:27:14,830 --> 00:27:16,060
Wait, stop for a second.

573
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:17,060
Just run.

574
00:27:28,140 --> 00:27:29,440
Stop right there!

575
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:02,820
Chen Haowei.

576
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:05,660
[Next Episode]

577
00:28:03,110 --> 00:28:04,410
So, he's the helper you hired?

578
00:28:04,410 --> 00:28:05,310
I can't even say my own name.

579
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,050
Why?

580
00:28:06,050 --> 00:28:06,850
You don't know him?

581
00:28:06,850 --> 00:28:07,280
Who?

582
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:08,110
You don't know him, either?

583
00:28:08,110 --> 00:28:08,980
No.

584
00:28:08,980 --> 00:28:09,920
It's the shooting star.

585
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:11,280
Didn't you make a wish yesterday?

586
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:12,450
Then why are you fine?

587
00:28:12,450 --> 00:28:14,020
Wishes don't affect me at all.

588
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:14,870
Li Wanzhe.

589
00:28:14,890 --> 00:28:16,120
I like you!

590
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:20,730
Have we met somewhere before?

